msgid "all"
msgstr "அனைத்தும்"

msgid "<b>Warnings:</b> %s"
msgstr "<b> எச்சரிக்கைகள்: </b> %s"

msgid ""
"Parameter estimates from the structural equation model, organized by type: "
"factor loadings, regression coefficients, variances, covariances, and "
"additional parameters."
msgstr ""

msgid "Factor Loadings"
msgstr "காரணி ஏற்றுதல்"

msgid ""
"Factor loadings from the measurement model (=~ operator). Each loading "
"reflects how strongly a latent variable is related to its observed "
"indicator. The first indicator loading is typically fixed to 1 to set the "
"scale of the latent variable."
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"Regression coefficients from the structural part of the model (~ operator). "
"These represent directed effects of predictors on outcomes among latent and/"
"or observed variables."
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"Estimated variances of the latent variables. For exogenous latent variables "
"these are total variances; for endogenous latent variables these are "
"residual variances (the variance not explained by predictors)."
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"Estimated covariances between latent variables (~~ operator). These "
"represent undirected associations between latent variables."
msgstr ""

msgid "Variables"
msgstr "மாறிகள்"

msgid ""
"Residual variances of the observed variables: the variance not explained by "
"the latent variables. Negative residual variances (Heywood cases) may "
"indicate model misspecification."
msgstr ""

#, fuzzy
msgid "Residual Covariances"
msgstr "மீதமுள்ள இணை வேறுபாடுகள்"

msgid ""
"Residual covariances between observed variables (~~ operator). These "
"represent correlated errors, i.e., shared variance between indicators not "
"accounted for by the latent variables."
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"Intercept (mean) parameters for observed and latent variables in the mean "
"structure. For observed variables, these are the expected values when all "
"predictors are zero."
msgstr ""

msgid "Missing data method 'FIML' forces meanstructure."
msgstr "காணாமல் போன தரவு முறை 'FIML' படைகள் என்பது கட்டமைப்பு என்று பொருள்."

msgid "Thresholds"
msgstr "வாசல்கள்"

msgid ""
"Threshold parameters for ordinal observed variables. These define the cut-"
"points on the underlying continuous distribution that separate the observed "
"categories."
msgstr ""

msgid "Threshold"
msgstr "வாசல்"

#, fuzzy
msgid "Defined Parameters"
msgstr "வரையறுக்கப்பட்ட அளவுருக்கள்"

msgid ""
"User-defined parameters specified with the := operator. These are functions "
"of existing model parameters, such as indirect effects or sums of "
"coefficients. Standard errors are computed using the Delta method."
msgstr ""

msgid "Name"
msgstr "பெயர்"

#, fuzzy
msgid "Indirect Effects"
msgstr "மறைமுக விளைவுகள்"

msgid ""
"Indirect effects of predictors on outcomes transmitted through mediating "
"variables. These are computed as the product of the path coefficients along "
"the indirect pathway."
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"Total effects combining direct and all indirect effects of predictors on "
"outcomes."
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"Additional model fit indices and information criteria for evaluating overall "
"model quality."
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"Model fit indices including incremental indices (CFI, TLI, NFI), absolute "
"indices (RMSEA, SRMR, GFI), and information criteria (AIC, BIC). Common "
"guidelines: CFI/TLI > .95, RMSEA < .06, SRMR < .08 indicate good fit, though "
"these should be interpreted cautiously."
msgstr ""

msgid "%s Fit indices are based on the scaled test statistic."
msgstr "%s FIT குறியீடுகள் அளவிடப்பட்ட சோதனை புள்ளிவிவரத்தை அடிப்படையாகக் கொண்டவை."

#, fuzzy
msgid "T-Size Fit Indices"
msgstr "டி-அளவு பொருத்தம் குறியீடுகள்"

msgid ""
"T-size equivalence testing fit indices (Marcoulides & Yuan, 2017). These "
"provide data-driven cutoff values for CFI and RMSEA that replace "
"conventional rules of thumb. The poor-fair and fair-close limits define "
"ranges for interpreting fit."
msgstr ""

msgid "Poor-fair limit"
msgstr "மோசமான-பல்வேறு வரம்பு"

msgid "Fair-close limit"
msgstr "நியாயமான நெருக்கமான வரம்பு"

msgid "T-size statistics are computed for <i>%s = 0.05</i>."
msgstr "டி-அளவு புள்ளிவிவரங்கள் <i>%s = 0.05 </i> க்கு கணக்கிடப்படுகின்றன."

msgid ""
"Proportion of variance in each endogenous variable explained by its "
"predictors in the model. Values range from 0 to 1, with higher values "
"indicating more variance explained."
msgstr ""

#, fuzzy
msgid "Average Variance Extracted"
msgstr "சராசரி மாறுபாடு பிரித்தெடுக்கப்பட்டது"

msgid ""
"Average Variance Extracted (AVE) measures the amount of variance captured by "
"a latent construct relative to measurement error. AVE values above 0.5 "
"indicate adequate convergent validity, meaning the construct explains more "
"than half the variance of its indicators."
msgstr ""

msgid "AVE"
msgstr "ஏவ்"

msgid "Reliability"
msgstr "நம்பகத்தன்மை"

msgid ""
"Composite reliability coefficients for each latent construct. Coefficient α "
"(alpha) assumes tau-equivalence (equal loadings), while coefficient ω "
"(omega) allows for congeneric indicators (unequal loadings) and is generally "
"preferred. Values above 0.7 are commonly considered acceptable."
msgstr ""

msgid "Coefficient α"
msgstr "குணகங்கள் α"

msgid "Coefficient ω"
msgstr "குணகங்கள்"

msgid "Heterotrait-Monotrait Ratio"
msgstr "ஈட்டோரோட்ரெய்ட்-மோனோட்ரேட் விகிதம்"

msgid ""
"Heterotrait-Monotrait (HTMT) ratio of correlations for assessing "
"discriminant validity. HTMT values below 0.85 (conservative) or 0.90 "
